HEADWORD: Hefty
<hw>Heft"y</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Moderately heavy.</def>
<mark>[Colloq. U. S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Strong; muscular; -- of people.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Substantial; large; <as>as, a <ex>hefty</ex>
increase in annual profits</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>hegari</ent>⟦br⟧
